  <summary date="2022-08-11T18:22:54Z" status="Introduced in Senate">Let Me Travel America Act

This bill prohibits operators of trains, buses, planes, and other common carriers that transport passengers interstate from denying service based on individuals' COVID-19 vaccination status. The bill also prohibits federal agencies from making COVID-19 vaccination a prerequisite for interstate travel.</summary>
